properties.title: Bremerton (City of)
properties.details: Over 17 years, City overhauled combined sewer overflow (CSO) control systems - resulting in reopening shellfish beds in Dyes Inlet to harvest. City achieved a 90% reduction in CSO events by 2000 at a cost of $18 Million.  By 2004, the City achieved a 97% reduction of CSO events for an additional $14.7 Million.  Since, the City has spent an additional $19.2 Million to reduce the remaining 3% of CSO events to the regulatory limit and to build in extra system capacity.  To date, the City has spent a total of $50 Million on CSO program improvements.
properties.description:
Waterway

Sinclair Inlet, Dyes Inlet

Type

Violation

Resolution

Settled

Details

Over 17 years, City overhauled combined sewer overflow (CSO) control systems - resulting in reopening shellfish beds in Dyes Inlet to harvest. City achieved a 90% reduction in CSO events by 2000 at a cost of $18 Million. By 2004, the City achieved a 97% reduction of CSO events for an additional $14.7 Million. Since, the City has spent an additional $19.2 Million to reduce the remaining 3% of CSO events to the regulatory limit and to build in extra system capacity. To date, the City has spent a total of $50 Million on CSO program improvements.
